Reinstall grub-efi

Download and Install grub-efi package, set the debian bootloader and create a grub config file based on your disk partitioning schema

    Install grub-efi package

# apt-get install --reinstall grub-efi

    Put the debian bootloader in /boot/efi and create an appropiate entry in the computerâ€™s UEFI Boot Manager

# grub-install /dev/sda

    Re create a grub config file based on your disk partitioning schema

# update-grub

reboot
